Class.Name: WKWebView
Class.Description: An object that displays interactive web content, such as for an in-app browser.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithFrame:configuration:
InstanceMethods.Description: Creates a web view and initializes it with the specified frame and configuration data.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithCoder:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns an object initialized from data in the specified coder object.

InstanceMethods.Name: loadRequest:
InstanceMethods.Description: Loads the web content referenced by the specified URL request object and navigates to it.

InstanceMethods.Name: loadHTMLString:baseURL:
InstanceMethods.Description: Loads the contents of the specified HTML string and navigates to it.

InstanceMethods.Name: loadFileURL:allowingReadAccessToURL:
InstanceMethods.Description: Loads the web content from the specified file and navigates to it.

InstanceMethods.Name: loadData:MIMEType:characterEncodingName:baseURL:
InstanceMethods.Description: Loads the content of the specified data object and navigates to it.

InstanceMethods.Name: reload
InstanceMethods.Description: Reloads the current webpage.

InstanceMethods.Name: reload:
InstanceMethods.Description: Reloads the current webpage.

InstanceMethods.Name: reloadFromOrigin
InstanceMethods.Description: Reloads the current webpage, and performs end-to-end revalidation of the content using cache-validating conditionals, if possible.

InstanceMethods.Name: reloadFromOrigin:
InstanceMethods.Description: Reloads the current webpage, and performs end-to-end revalidation of the content using cache-validating conditionals, if possible.

InstanceMethods.Name: stopLoading
InstanceMethods.Description: Stops loading all resources on the current page.

InstanceMethods.Name: stopLoading:
InstanceMethods.Description: Stops loading all resources on the current page.

InstanceMethods.Name: setMagnification:centeredAtPoint:
InstanceMethods.Description: Scales the page content and centers the result on the specified point.

InstanceMethods.Name: findString:withConfiguration:completionHandler:
InstanceMethods.Description: Searches for the specified string in the web view’s content.

InstanceMethods.Name: goBack:
InstanceMethods.Description: Navigates to the back item in the back-forward list.

InstanceMethods.Name: goBack
InstanceMethods.Description: Navigates to the back item in the back-forward list.

InstanceMethods.Name: goForward:
InstanceMethods.Description: Navigates to the forward item in the back-forward list.

InstanceMethods.Name: goForward
InstanceMethods.Description: Navigates to the forward item in the back-forward list.

InstanceMethods.Name: goToBackForwardListItem:
InstanceMethods.Description: Navigates to an item from the back-forward list and sets it as the current item.

InstanceMethods.Name: evaluateJavaScript:completionHandler:
InstanceMethods.Description: Evaluates the specified JavaScript string.

InstanceMethods.Name: evaluateJavaScript:inFrame:inContentWorld:completionHandler:
InstanceMethods.Description: Evaluates the specified JavaScript string in the specified frame and content world.

InstanceMethods.Name: callAsyncJavaScript:arguments:inFrame:inContentWorld:completionHandler:
InstanceMethods.Description: Executes the specified string as an asynchronous JavaScript function.

InstanceMethods.Name: takeSnapshotWithConfiguration:completionHandler:
InstanceMethods.Description: Generates a platform-native image from the web view’s contents asynchronously.

InstanceMethods.Name: createPDFWithConfiguration:completionHandler:
InstanceMethods.Description: Generates PDF data from the web view’s contents asynchronously.

InstanceMethods.Name: createWebArchiveDataWithCompletionHandler:
InstanceMethods.Description: Creates a web archive of the web view’s contents asynchronously.

InstanceMethods.Name: printOperationWithPrintInfo:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the print operation object to use when printing the contents of the web view.

InstanceProperties.Name: configuration
InstanceProperties.Description: The object that contains the configuration details for the web view.

InstanceProperties.Name: UIDelegate
InstanceProperties.Description: The object you use to integrate custom user interface elements, such as contextual menus or panels, into web view interactions.

InstanceProperties.Name: navigationDelegate
InstanceProperties.Description: The object you use to manage navigation behavior for the web view.

InstanceProperties.Name: loading
InstanceProperties.Description: A Boolean value that indicates whether the view is currently loading content.

InstanceProperties.Name: estimatedProgress
InstanceProperties.Description: An estimate of what fraction of the current navigation has been loaded.

InstanceProperties.Name: scrollView
InstanceProperties.Description: The scroll view associated with the web view.

InstanceProperties.Name: title
InstanceProperties.Description: The page title.

InstanceProperties.Name: URL
InstanceProperties.Description: The URL for the current webpage.

InstanceProperties.Name: mediaType
InstanceProperties.Description: The media type for the contents of the web view.

InstanceProperties.Name: customUserAgent
InstanceProperties.Description: The custom user agent string.

InstanceProperties.Name: serverTrust
InstanceProperties.Description: The trust management object you use to evaluate trust for the current webpage.

InstanceProperties.Name: hasOnlySecureContent
InstanceProperties.Description: A Boolean value that indicates whether the web view loaded all resources on the page through securely encrypted connections.

InstanceProperties.Name: pageZoom
InstanceProperties.Description: The scale factor by which the web view scales content relative to its bounds.

InstanceProperties.Name: allowsMagnification
InstanceProperties.Description: A Boolean value that indicates whether magnify gestures change the web view’s magnification.

InstanceProperties.Name: magnification
InstanceProperties.Description: The factor by which the page content is currently scaled.

InstanceProperties.Name: allowsBackForwardNavigationGestures
InstanceProperties.Description: A Boolean value that indicates whether horizontal swipe gestures trigger backward and forward page navigation.

InstanceProperties.Name: backForwardList
InstanceProperties.Description: The web view's back-forward list.

InstanceProperties.Name: canGoBack
InstanceProperties.Description: A Boolean value that indicates whether there is a valid back item in the back-forward list.

InstanceProperties.Name: canGoForward
InstanceProperties.Description: A Boolean value that indicates whether there is a valid forward item in the back-forward list.

InstanceProperties.Name: allowsLinkPreview
InstanceProperties.Description: A Boolean value that determines whether pressing a link displays a preview of the destination for the link.

InstanceProperties.Name: certificateChain
InstanceProperties.Description: An array of objects forming the certificate chain for the currently committed navigation.

TypeMethods.Name: handlesURLScheme:
TypeMethods.Description: Returns a Boolean value that indicates whether WebKit natively supports resources with the specified URL scheme.
